Pupa. Thoracic respiratory organ rather short, club–shaped, widest medially, not constricted subapically (
Fig. 9d
); length 844 (773–925), width 243 (214–284), length/width 3.48 (2.92–4.0, n=18). Lateral ribs of terminal processes slightly paler than middle rib.

